Åsnen.label: Åsnen
Åsnen.description: Åsnen is a large lake in southern Småland, Sweden, roughly 150 km² in size. The river Mörrumsån flows south from Åsnen into the Baltic Sea. Wikipedia

Śniardwy.label: Śniardwy
Śniardwy.description: Śniardwy is a lake in the Masurian Lake District of the Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, Poland. It is the largest lake in Poland with an area of 113.8 square kilometres. It is 22.1 kilometres long and 13.4 kilometres wide. Wikipedia

Aalkistensee.label: Aalkistensee
Aalkistensee.description: Aalkistensee is a lake in Kraichgau, Baden-Württemberg, Germany. At an elevation of ca 250 m, its surface area is 0.136 km². Wikipedia

Öskjuvatn.label: Öskjuvatn
Öskjuvatn.description: Öskjuvatn is a lake in the Highlands of Iceland. Its surface area is about 11 km². With a depth of 217 m, it is the second deepest lake in Iceland after Jökulsárlón. Wikipedia

Černé jezero.label: Černé jezero
Černé jezero.description:
Černé jezero in the Bohemian Forest is the largest and deepest natural lake in the Czech Republic.
This triangular lake surrounded with spruce forest is located about 6 km northwest of Železná Ruda under a 300-metre-high cliff on Jezerní hora. Wikipedia

Štěchovice Reservoir.label: Štěchovice Reservoir
Štěchovice Reservoir.description: Štěchovice Reservoir is a dam on Vltava River built during 1937 - 1945 as the second stage of the Vltava Cascade. The dam is named after nearby village Štěchovice. Wikipedia

Aasee (Bocholt).label: Aasee
Aasee (Bocholt).description: Aasee is a lake in Bocholt, Kreis Borken, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 23.8 meter, its surface area is 0.32 km². Wikipedia

Akkajaure.label: Akkajaure
Akkajaure.description: Akkajaure is one of the largest reservoirs in Sweden. It lies at the headwaters of the Lule River in Norrbotten County, in Swedish Lappland, within the Stora Sjöfallet national park. Wikipedia

Achit Lake.label: Achit Lake
Achit Lake.description: Achit Lake is the largest freshwater lake in the Uvs Aimag of Mongolia, in the west of the country. At an elevation of 1,435 m above sea level it covers an area of 290 km². It is 28 km long, 16 km wide, and 10 m deep. Wikipedia

Allner See.label: Allner See
Allner See.description: Allner See is a lake in Rhein-Sieg-Kreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 63,5 m, its surface area is 0.10 km². Wikipedia

Alplersee.label: Alplersee
Alplersee.description:
Alplersee is a lake on the slopes of the Rophaien mountain near Riemenstalden and Sisikon in the Canton of Uri, Switzerland.
There is another lake in the canton of Uri with the same name near Unterschächen. Wikipedia

Aibi Lake.label: Aibi Lake
Aibi Lake.description: Aibi Lake is a rift lake in north west China, near the border to Kazakhstan. Lying at the southeast end of the Dzungarian Gate, it is the catchment center of the southwestern part of the Dzungarian Basin. Wikipedia

Arlesheimer See.label: Arlesheimer See
Arlesheimer See.description: Arlesheimer See is a lake in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. At an elevation of 212 m, its surface area is 0.060 km². Wikipedia

Argazi Reservoir.label: Argazi Reservoir
Argazi Reservoir.description: Argazi Reservoir is a reservoir, created on the Miass River in Chelyabinsk Oblast in 1946. The Argazi Lake has become a part of the Argazi Reservoir ever since. The reservoir has a surface area of 102 km² and a water volume of 0,65 cubic km. Wikipedia

Artillery Lake.label: Artillery Lake
Artillery Lake.description: Artillery Lake is a lake in the Northwest Territories, Canada about 20 miles east of Great Slave Lake. George Back reached it in 1834. Wikipedia

Aydar Lake.label: Aydar Lake
Aydar Lake.description: The Aydar Lake is part of the man-made Aydar-Arnasay system of lakes, which covers an area of 4,000 square kilometres. This system includes 3 brackish water lakes located in the saline depressions of the south-eastern Kyzyl Kum. Wikipedia

Baberowsee.label: Baberowsee
Baberowsee.description: Baberowsee is a lake in Brandenburg, Germany. It is located in Kagel, an Ortsteil of the municipality of Grünheide, Oder-Spree district. Wikipedia

Bachalpsee.label: Bachalpsee
Bachalpsee.description: Bachalpsee or Bachse is a lake with an area of 8.06 ha close to the First above Grindelwald in the Bernese Oberland, Switzerland. The lake, located at an elevation of 2,265 m, is split by a natural dam, the smaller part of the lake being 6 m lower. Wikipedia

Baker Lake (Washington).label: Baker Lake
Baker Lake (Washington).description: Baker Lake is a lake in northern Washington state in the United States. The lake is situated in the Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest and Baker River valley southwest of North Cascades National ... Wikipedia

Bala Lake.label: Bala Lake
Bala Lake.description: Bala Lake is a large lake in Gwynedd, Wales. It was the largest natural body of water in Wales prior to the level being raised by Thomas Telford to help support the flow of the Ellesmere Canal. Wikipedia

Behler See.label: Behler See
Behler See.description: The Behler See is a lake in the Holstein Switzerland region of North Germany. It lies between Timmdorf to the east and the town of Plön to the west. To the east it transitions into the Langensee, to the west into the Höftsee. Wikipedia

Blackbrook Reservoir.label: Blackbrook Reservoir
Blackbrook Reservoir.description: Blackbrook Reservoir is a large body of water near Shepshed, Leicestershire, in England. The reservoir was constructed in 1796 in order to feed the Charnwood Forest Canal, which has long since vanished. Wikipedia

Bolzer See.label: Bolzer See
Bolzer See.description: Bolzer See is a lake in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. At an elevation of 31.6 m, its surface area is 0.81 km². Wikipedia

Breiðárlón.label: Breiðárlón
Breiðárlón.description:
Breiðárlón is a glacier lake at the south end of the Icelandic glacier Vatnajökull.
The glacier calving into the lagoon is a part of Vatnajökull National Park and the better known glacier lake Jökulsárlón is not far from there. Wikipedia

Brennersee.label: Brennersee
Brennersee.description: The lake Brennersee lies approximately 1.15 km north of the Brenner Pass, 1310 metres above sea level. With an area of approximately 19 ha, it is the biggest lake in the Wipptal. Wikipedia

Cambser See.label: Cambser See
Cambser See.description: Cambser See is a lake in Nordwestmecklenburg, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. At an elevation of 30.9 m, its surface area is 2.85 km². Wikipedia

Casteilla.label: Casteilla
Casteilla.description: Casteilla or Estany de la Castella is a lake in Pyrénées-Orientales, Pyrénées, France. At an elevation of 2280 m, its surface area is 0.05 km². Wikipedia

Cayuga Lake.label: Cayuga Lake
Cayuga Lake.description: Cayuga Lake is the longest of central New York's glacial Finger Lakes, and is the second largest in surface area and second largest in volume. It is just under 40 miles long. Wikipedia

Chatyr-Kul.label: Chatyr-Kul
Chatyr-Kul.description: Chatyr-Kul is an endorheic alpine lake in the Tian Shan mountains in At-Bashi District of Naryn Province, Kyrgyzstan; it lies in the lower part of Chatyr-Kul Depression near the Torugart Pass border crossing into China. Wikipedia

Colico Lake.label: Colico Lake
Colico Lake.description: Colico Lake is located in the La Araucanía Region of Chile. The neighboring Caburgua Lake lies to the east of the lake and the Villarrica Lake to the south. Wikipedia

Cockshoot Broad.label: Cockshoot Broad
Cockshoot Broad.description: Cockshoot Broad, one of the Norfolk Broads, lies on the River Bure within The Broads National Park in Norfolk, England. It is one of several Broads where boats are not allowed at any time of the year, although they can moor at its entrance. Wikipedia

Cree Lake.label: Cree Lake
Cree Lake.description: Cree Lake is a lake in Saskatchewan, Canada. The lake is the fourth largest in the province and is located west of Reindeer Lake and south of Lake Athabasca. There is no highway access, but the lake is reachable by float plane. Wikipedia

Dörgön Lake.label: Dörgön Lake
Dörgön Lake.description: Dörgön Lake is a saltwater lake in Khovd, Mongolia. It is a part of the Great Lakes Depression, being one of the remnants of a prehistoric lake. It has a salinity of 4%. Wikipedia

Amsoldingersee.label: Amsoldingersee
Amsoldingersee.description: Amsoldingersee is small lake adjacent to the town of Amsoldingen, in the Upper Gürbetal. It is located near the city of Thun, Switzerland. The lake has a surface area of 38 hectares and a maximum length of 1.1 km and width of 500 m. Wikipedia

Czarny Staw pod Rysami.label: Czarny Staw pod Rysami
Czarny Staw pod Rysami.description: Czarny Staw pod Rysami is a mountain lake on the Polish side of Mount Rysy in the Tatra mountains. At 1,583 m above sea level, it overlooks the nearby lake of Morskie Oko. Its maximum depth is 76 m. Wikipedia

Derwent Reservoir (Derbyshire).label: Derwent Reservoir
Derwent Reservoir (Derbyshire).description: Derwent Reservoir is the middle of three reservoirs in the Upper Derwent Valley in the northeast of Derbyshire, England. It lies approximately 10 miles from Glossop and 10 miles from Sheffield. Wikipedia

Dian Lake.label: Dian Lake
Dian Lake.description: Dianchi Lake, also known as Lake Dian and Kunming Lake, is a large endorheic lake located on the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau close to Kunming, Yunnan, in southern China. Wikipedia

Dongting Lake.label: Dongting Lake
Dongting Lake.description: Dongting Lake, or Lake Dongting is a large, shallow lake in northeastern Hu'nan province, China. It is a flood basin of the Yangtze River. Hence the lake's size depends on the season. Wikipedia

Dniprodzerzhynsk Reservoir.label: Dniprodzerzhynsk Reservoir
Dniprodzerzhynsk Reservoir.description: The Dniprodzerzhynsk Reservoir is a water reservoir located on the lower part of the Dnieper River in Ukraine. Named after the city of Dniprodzerzhynsk, it covers a total area of 567 square kilometres within the Dnipropetrovsk Oblast. Wikipedia

Drawsko Lake.label: Drawsko Lake
Drawsko Lake.description: Drawsko is a lake in Drawskie Lakeland, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, Poland. It is 1,956 ha large, 12,6 km long and 3.9 km wide. Maximum depth is 79.7 m, making it the second deepest lake in Poland. Wikipedia

Faaker See.label: Lake Faak
Faaker See.description: Lake Faak or Faaker See is an alpine lake in the Austrian state of Carinthia. With an area of approximately 2.2 km², it is the state's fifth-largest lake. Lake Faak is a popular vacation and swimming destination, known for its clear turquoise water. Wikipedia

Emma Lake (Saskatchewan).label: Emma Lake
Emma Lake (Saskatchewan).description: Emma Lake is a combined campground, and lake. The area has a population of around 900 in the summertime, and 200 in the wintertime. Emma Lake is 45 kilometers north of Prince Albert, Saskatchewan and 5 kilometers from Christopher Lake, Saskatchewan. Wikipedia

Fjallavatn.label: Fjallavatn
Fjallavatn.description: Fjallavatn is the second largest lake in the Faroe Islands. It is situated on the island of Vágar and its size is 1 km². Wikipedia

Fjallsárlón.label: Fjallsárlón
Fjallsárlón.description: Fjallsárlón is a glacier lake at the south end of the Icelandic glacier Vatnajökull. Fjallsjökull which is part of the bigger glacier reaches down to the water of the lake and some ice-bergs are drifting by on its surface. Wikipedia

Forggensee.label: Forggensee
Forggensee.description: Forggensee is a lake located north of Füssen in the district of Ostallgäu in Bavaria, Germany. One of many lakes in the region around Hohenschwangau and Neuschwanstein castles, Forggensee is the ... Wikipedia

Funtensee.label: Funtensee
Funtensee.description: Funtensee is a lake in the Steinernes Meer plateau in the Nationalpark Berchtesgaden, Bavaria, Germany located on the larger of the two sinkholes of the uvala, known for record low temperatures up to 30°C lower than the surrounding area. Wikipedia

Franklin D. Roosevelt Lake.label: Franklin D. Roosevelt Lake
Franklin D. Roosevelt Lake.description: Franklin D. Roosevelt Lake is the reservoir created in 1941 by the impoundment of the Columbia River by the Grand Coulee Dam in Washington state. It is named for Franklin D. Roosevelt, who was President during the construction of the dam. Wikipedia

Fuschlsee.label: Fuschlsee
Fuschlsee.description: Fuschlsee is a lake in the Salzkammergut, Austria, located at 47°48′10″N 13°16′20″E﻿ / ﻿47.80278°N 13.27222°E. Its surface is approximately 2.7 km² and its maximum depth is 66 metres. Wikipedia

Garrensee.label: Garrensee
Garrensee.description: Garrensee is a lake in Ziethen, Kreis Herzogtum Lauenburg, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. Wikipedia

Gatun Lake.label: Gatun Lake
Gatun Lake.description: Gatun Lake is a large artificial lake to the south of Colón, Panama. It forms a major part of the Panama Canal, carrying ships for 33 km of their transit across the Isthmus of Panama. Wikipedia

Glattalpsee.label: Glattalpsee
Glattalpsee.description: Glattalpsee is a lake on Glattalp, above Bisisthal, in the municipality of Muotathal, Canton of Schwyz, Switzerland. Its surface area is 0.39 km². Wikipedia

Gelmersee.label: Gelmersee
Gelmersee.description: Gelmersee is a lake in Bernese Oberland, Switzerland. The hydroelectric reservoir was built at the same time as Grimselsee. The reservoir's volume is 13 million m³ and its surface area 0.645 km². Wikipedia

Gopło.label: Gopło
Gopło.description: Gopło is a lake in Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship, north-central Poland, near the city of Gniezno. It gives its name to the protected area called Gopło Landscape Park. Wikipedia

Grænalón.label: Grænalón
Grænalón.description: Grænalón is one of the glacier lakes of the Icelandic glacier Vatnajökull. It is situated in the south of Iceland. Its surface measures 18 km². Wikipedia

Gothensee.label: Gothensee
Gothensee.description: Gothensee is a lake in Usedom, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. At an elevation of 0 m, its surface area is 5.56 km². Wikipedia

Great Bear Lake.label: Great Bear Lake
Great Bear Lake.description: Great Bear Lake is the largest lake entirely in Canada, the fourth largest in North America, and the eighth largest in the world. Wikipedia

Great Slave Lake.label: Great Slave Lake
Great Slave Lake.description: Great Slave Lake is the second-largest lake in the Northwest Territories of Canada, the deepest lake in North America at 614 metres, and the tenth-largest lake in the world. It is 480 km long and 19 to 109 km wide. Wikipedia

Grevelingen.label: Grevelingen
Grevelingen.description: Grevelingen or Grevelingenmeer is a former Rhine-Meuse estuary on the border of the Dutch provinces of South Holland and Zeeland that has become a lake due to the Delta Works. Wikipedia

Greifensee.label: Greifensee
Greifensee.description: Greifensee is a small lake in the canton of Zürich in Switzerland. Wikipedia

Grimnitzsee.label: Grimnitzsee
Grimnitzsee.description: Grimnitzsee is a lake in Landkreis Barnim, Brandenburg, Germany. At an elevation of 64 m, its surface area is 7.8 km². It is situated in the municipality of Joachimsthal. Wikipedia

Grimselsee.label: Grimselsee
Grimselsee.description: Grimselsee or Lake Grimsel is an artificial lake near Grimsel pass in the Canton of Berne, Switzerland. With a volume of 95 mio m³, it is larger than other hydroelectric reservoirs in the region Oberaarsee, Räterichsbodensee and Gelmersee. Wikipedia

Großer Wannsee.label: Großer Wannsee
Großer Wannsee.description: The Großer Wannsee is a bight of the Havel river near the locality of Wannsee and Nikolassee, a south-western suburb of the German capital Berlin not far from Potsdam. Wikipedia

Großer Wummsee.label: Großer Wummsee
Großer Wummsee.description: Großer Wummsee is a lake in Landkreis Ostprignitz-Ruppin, Brandenburg, Germany. At an elevation of 61,0 m, its surface area is 1.52 km². Wikipedia

Höytiäinen.label: Höytiäinen
Höytiäinen.description: Höytiäinen is a lake in Finland. A mismanaged drainage attempt during 1859, the lake was by around one third of its size. Wikipedia

Gudelacksee.label: Gudelacksee
Gudelacksee.description: Gudelacksee is a German lake in Lindow, Landkreis Ostprignitz-Ruppin, Brandenburg. At an elevation of 52 m, its surface area is 4.38 km². Wikipedia

Hücker Moor.label: Hücker Moor
Hücker Moor.description: Hücker Moor is a lake in Hücker-Aschen, Spenge, Kreis Herford, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 62.7 m, its surface area is 10.9 ha. Wikipedia

Haidersee.label: Haidersee
Haidersee.description: The Haidersee is a lake in South Tyrol, Italy, which belongs to the municipality of Graun im Vinschgau. Wikipedia

Hainer See.label: Hainer See
Hainer See.description: Hainer See is a lake near Borna, Saxony, Germany. At an elevation of 126 m, its surface area is 4 km². Wikipedia

Hanhowuz Reservoir.label: Hanhowuz Reservoir
Hanhowuz Reservoir.description: Hanhowuz, also known as Khauz-Khan is a reservoir in Mary Province of southeastern Turkmenistan. It is located at 37°13′56″N 61°14′37″E﻿ / ﻿37.23222°N 61.24361°E. The M37 highway passes nearby and the village of Hanhowuz stands on the northwestern ... Wikipedia

Helenesee.label: Helenesee
Helenesee.description: Helenesee is a lake in Brandenburg, Germany. Its surface area is ca. 250 ha. With a depth of 56.63 m, the Helenseee is the second deepest lake in Brandenburg, only surpassed by the lake Großer Stechlinsee. Wikipedia

Hopfensee.label: Hopfensee
Hopfensee.description:
Hopfensee is a lake in Bayerisch Schwaben, Bavaria, Germany. At an elevation of 783.8 m, its surface area is 194 ha.
The maximum length of the lake is 2.1 km, and its circumference is 6.8 km. It lies north of Füssen in Ostallgäu. Wikipedia

Hreðavatn.label: Hreðavatn
Hreðavatn.description: Hreðavatn is a lake in the west of Iceland. It is situated near Route 1 between Borgarnes and the pass of Holtavörtuheiði. Nearby is the university faculty of Bifröst and the Grábrók craters as well as the mountain Baula. Wikipedia

Hulun Lake.label: Hulun Lake
Hulun Lake.description: Hulun Lake or Dalai Lake, is a lake in Inner Mongolia, China. It is one of the five largest freshwater lakes in all of China, covering approximately 2,339 km². Wikipedia

Hornindalsvatnet.label: Hornindalsvatnet
Hornindalsvatnet.description: Hornindalsvatnet is Norway's and Europe's deepest lake, officially measured to a depth of 514 metres. Its surface is 53 metres above sea level, which means that its bottom is 461 metres below sea level. Wikipedia

Kakhovka Reservoir.label: Kakhovka Reservoir
Kakhovka Reservoir.description: The Kakhovka Reservoir is a water reservoir located on the Dnieper River. It covers a total surface area of 2,155 square kilometres in the territories of the Kherson, Zaporizhia, and the Dnipropetrovsk Oblasts of Ukraine. Wikipedia

Kallavesi.label: Kallavesi
Kallavesi.description: Kallavesi is a medium-sized lake in Northern Savonia, eastern Finland located around the town of Kuopio. Wikipedia

Kanas Lake.label: Kanas Lake
Kanas Lake.description: Kanas Lake is a lake in Altay Prefecture, Xinjiang, China. The lake is located in a valley in the Altai Mountains, near the very northern tip of Xinjiang, and the province's borders with Kazakhstan, Mongolia, and Russia. Wikipedia

Kamloops Lake.label: Kamloops Lake
Kamloops Lake.description: Kamloops Lake in British Columbia, Canada is situated on the Thompson River just west of Kamloops. The lake is 1.6 km wide, 29 km long, and up to 152 m deep. The community of Savona is located at the west end of the lake on the Thompson River. Wikipedia

Karakul (Tajikistan).label: Karakul
Karakul (Tajikistan).description: Karakul or Qarokul, is a 52 km diameter lake in the Pamir Mountains in Tajikistan. It lies within the Tajik National Park. Wikipedia

Katzensee.label: Katzensee
Katzensee.description: Katzensee is a lake on the border of the city of Zurich and Regensdorf in the Canton of Zurich, Switzerland. Wikipedia

Klöntalersee.label: Klöntalersee
Klöntalersee.description: Klöntalersee is a natural lake in the Canton of Glarus, Switzerland. Since 1908, it has been used as a reservoir for electricity production. The dam's construction substantially increased the lake's volume. Wikipedia

Kleifarvatn.label: Kleifarvatn
Kleifarvatn.description: Kleifarvatn is the largest lake on the Reykjanes peninsula in Iceland, situated in the southern part of the peninsula on the fissure zone of the Mid-Atlantic Ridge. Wikipedia

Kluane Lake.label: Kluane Lake
Kluane Lake.description: Kluane Lake is located in the southwest area of the Yukon. At approximately 400 km², and 70 km long, it is the largest lake contained entirely within the territorial border. Wikipedia

Kochelsee.label: Kochelsee
Kochelsee.description: Kochelsee or Lake Kochel is located 70 kilometres south of Munich on the edge of the Bavarian Alps. The western third of the lake lies within the borders of the town of Schlehdorf, while the rest belongs to Kochel am See. Wikipedia

Kurile Lake.label: Kurile Lake
Kurile Lake.description:
Kurile Lake is a large caldera containing a crater lake located at the southern tip of Kamchatka Peninsula, within the Southern Kamchatka Wildlife Refuge in Russia.
It has an area of 77 square kilometres. Wikipedia

Lac Brenet.label: Lac Brenet
Lac Brenet.description: Lac Brenet is a lake in the Vallée de Joux, canton of Vaud, Switzerland. It is located north of the Lac de Joux, only 200 metres away. Its elevation of 1002 metres is 2 metres below that of Lac de Joux. Wikipedia

Kootenay Lake.label: Kootenay Lake
Kootenay Lake.description: Kootenay Lake is a lake located in British Columbia, Canada and is part of the Kootenay River. The lake has been raised by the Corra Linn Dam and has a dike system at the southern end, which, along with ... Wikipedia

Dittligsee.label: Dittligsee
Dittligsee.description: Dittligsee is a lake in the Canton of Berne, Switzerland, near Blumenstein and Wattenwil. Its surface area is 6.02 ha. Wikipedia

Lac de Montsalvens.label: Lac de Montsalvens
Lac de Montsalvens.description: Lac de Montsalvens is a lake in the Canton of Fribourg, Switzerland. The reservoir has a capacity of 12.6 million m³ and a surface area of 0.74 km². It is located on the road to Jaun Pass, between the villages of Broc and Charmey. Wikipedia

Lac de Gérardmer.label: Lac de Gérardmer
Lac de Gérardmer.description: Lac de Gérardmer is a lake at Gérardmer, Vosges, France. At an elevation of 660 m, its surface area is 1.16 km². Wikipedia

Lac Noir (Vosges).label: Lac Noir
Lac Noir (Vosges).description: Lac Noir is a lake in Orbey, Alsace, France. At an elevation of 955 m, its surface area is 0.14 km². Wikipedia

Lac de Tseuzier.label: Lac de Tseuzier
Lac de Tseuzier.description: Lac de Tseuzier is an artificial lake in the canton of Valais, Switzerland. It is located in the municipalities of Ayent and Icogne. The reservoir has a volume of 51 mio m³ and a surface area of 0.85 km². Wikipedia

Lac des Brenets.label: Lac des Brenets
Lac des Brenets.description: Lac des Brenets or Lac de Chaillexon is a lake on the Doubs River on the border of Switzerland and France. Wikipedia

Adolfosee.label: Adolfosee
Adolfosee.description: Adolfosee is a lake in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 39 m, its surface area is 0.307 km². Wikipedia
